Reasoning: The paper describes a novel algorithm for constructing the string graph for de novo assembly of reads data, which involves data structures and algorithms commonly used in computational biology and bioinformatics. The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm on a standard benchmark, which suggests a focus on efficiency and optimization. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) due to the use of parallel processing and the potential applications of the algorithm in analyzing large-scale genomic data.
